 Usage instructions

Detailed information on how this workflow operates.

 Dependencies

List any system libraries or binaries that this workflow needs installed. Special privileges the user needs (ie. root, sudo) can also be listed here.

 Results verification

List any steps that can be performed to check the outcome of the workflow.

 Notification plan

Define who should be notified when the workflow succeeds and fails.
 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    Backup Options - ie\: "COMPRESSION"
    Databases - If blank, all databases are backed up.  If "SYSTEM", only system databases are backed up.  If "NONE", no backups are taken.
    Instance Password - No description
    Instance User Domain - No description
    Instance Username - No description
    Instance.Name - No description
    Server.Name - No description
    Subdirectory Name - If specified, a subdirectory will be created within the instance's default backup path, and backup files will be stored there.
    Target Instances - No description

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Backup Type - optional - backup type; valid values are FULL, LOG, DIFFERENTIAL, COPY-ONLY, COPY-ONLY LOG.  If none is provided, FULL backup will be taken.
    Backup Path - optional - path to store backup files.  If none is provided, step will use backup directory value indicated in SQL Server's server settings.

The list of databases to backup can range from all databases (default), all except a select few (ignore list), or just a select few (exclusive list). There's Inputs\: command - executes MSSQLBackupDatabases.py Backup Options - ie\: "COMPRESSION" Backup Path - optional - path to store backup files. If none is provided, step will use backup directory value indicated in SQL Server's server settings. Backup Type - optional - backup type; valid values are FULL, LOG, DIFFERENTIAL, COPY-ONLY, COPY-ONLY LOG. If none is provided, FULL backup will be taken. Databases - If blank, all databases are backed up. If "SYSTEM", only system databases are backed up. If "NONE", no backups are taken. Instance Password - No description Instance User Domain - No description Instance Username - No description Subdirectory Name - If specified, a subdirectory will be created within the instance's default backup path, and backup files will be stored there. Results\: List of Backup Files - A comma-delimited list of the backup files (including their paths) that were created. Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
